[19:53] <brtastic> aah :D thanks

[19:54] <guifa> sub foo (Str:D $a) {¬†‚Ä¶¬†}  <‚Äî have to pass a defiend string

[19:54] <guifa> sub foo (Str:U $a) { ‚Ä¶ }  <‚Äî have to pass an undefined string (basically, a type object for Str or a subclass)

[19:55] <guifa> sub foo (Str:_ $a) { ‚Ä¶ }  <‚Äî explicitly don‚Äôt care (but that‚Äôs the default so there‚Äôs no real reason to ever use it, except maybe to indicate that you *really* do accept both if you‚Äôre strongly typing)

[19:55] *** |oLa| joined
[19:55] <moon-child> what's the difference between :D and :D:?

